<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1644,2031]" pageId="14" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1645,1671]" pageId="14" pageNumber="43">Remarks</emphasis>
. According to the keys of 
<bibRefCitation author="Dirsh" box="[610,757,1644,1671]" pageId="14" pageNumber="43" pagination="299 - 400" refId="ref11934" refString="Dirsh V. M. (1958) Revision of the group Portheti (Orthoptera: Acridoidea). Eos, Revista espanola de Entomologia, 34, 299 - 400" type="journal article" year="1958">Dirsh (1958)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hemp, C." box="[770,921,1645,1671]" pageId="14" pageNumber="43" pagination="295 - 300" refId="ref12175" refString="Hemp, C. (2013) A new Lobosceliana Dirsh species (Orthoptera: Pamphagidae: Porthetinae) from coastal Tanzania, East Africa. Zootaxa, 3731 (2), 295 - 300. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3731.2.10" type="journal article" year="2013">Hemp (2013)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Rowell, C. H. F. &amp; Hemp, C. &amp; Harvey, A. W." box="[977,1205,1644,1671]" pageId="14" pageNumber="43" refId="ref12736" refString="Rowell, C. H. F., Hemp, C., Harvey, A. W. (2015) Jago's Grasshoppers of East and North East Africa. Vol. 1. Blurb, 238 pp." type="book" year="2015">
Rowell 
<emphasis box="[1066,1116,1645,1671]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="43">et al</emphasis>
. (2015)
</bibRefCitation>
in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Dirsh, 1958" authorityName="Dirsh" authorityYear="1958" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Lobosceliana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="43">Lobosceliana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dirsh" box="[242,375,1680,1707]" pageId="14" pageNumber="43" pagination="299 - 400" refId="ref11934" refString="Dirsh V. M. (1958) Revision of the group Portheti (Orthoptera: Acridoidea). Eos, Revista espanola de Entomologia, 34, 299 - 400" type="journal article" year="1958">Dirsh, 1958</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
the medial part of antenna consists of two clearly divided segments, and the upper margin of the hind femur is straight, while in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Dirsh, 1958" authorityName="Dirsh" authorityYear="1958" box="[658,950,1716,1743]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Xiphoceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[658,810,1717,1743]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="43">Xiphoceriana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dirsh" box="[818,950,1716,1743]" pageId="14" pageNumber="43" pagination="299 - 400" refId="ref11934" refString="Dirsh V. M. (1958) Revision of the group Portheti (Orthoptera: Acridoidea). Eos, Revista espanola de Entomologia, 34, 299 - 400" type="journal article" year="1958">Dirsh, 1958</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
the medial part of the antenna consists of a single segment (sometimes with a faint trace of division in two) and the upper margin of the hind femur is slightly incurved in front of the knee. However, the specimens above listed may belong to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dirsh" authorityYear="1958" box="[1203,1354,1789,1815]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Lobosceliana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1203,1354,1789,1815]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="43">Lobosceliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the medial part of antenna, and to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dirsh" authorityYear="1958" box="[599,751,1825,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Xiphoceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[599,751,1825,1851]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="43">Xiphoceriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the upper margin of hind femur which is incurved in front of the knee. Actually the two genera are difficult to separate (C. Hemp, pers. comm.), only clear differences are in the male genitalia (
<bibRefCitation author="Rowell, C. H. F. &amp; Hemp, C. &amp; Harvey, A. W." box="[364,577,1896,1923]" pageId="14" pageNumber="43" refId="ref12736" refString="Rowell, C. H. F., Hemp, C., Harvey, A. W. (2015) Jago's Grasshoppers of East and North East Africa. Vol. 1. Blurb, 238 pp." type="book" year="2015">
Rowell 
<emphasis box="[454,503,1897,1923]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="43">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
); probably they are synonyms. The size of the four males is given in 
<tableCitation box="[1346,1431,1897,1923]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="15.[151,239,154,178]" captionText="TABLE 3. Measurements (range) of unidentified males of the genus Xiphoceriana Dirsh, 1958 or Lobosceliana Dirsh, 1958. TL = Total length of body; LP = Length of pronotum; HP = Height of pronotum; LHF = Length of hind femora; DHF = Depth of hind femora. TL LP HP LHF DHF LP/LHF LP/HP 30.1-31.0 12.0-13.0 9.2-9.5 11.8-12.5 4.1-4.5 1.0-1.1 1.3-1.4" pageId="14" pageNumber="43">Table 3</tableCitation>
; only 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gerstaecker" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[207,295,1934,1959]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Xiphoceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atrox">
<emphasis box="[207,295,1934,1959]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="43">X. atrox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above) has a similar size, but it differs by the shape of pronotum (compare Figs. 45 and 46). Thus, considering the high number of the species described, the number of synonyms and the scarcity of material belonging to the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1916" box="[383,511,2005,2031]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Porthetinae">Porthetinae</taxonomicName>
preserved in the collections, for the moment they remain unidentified.
</paragraph>
